oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Giles County Hospital staff
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group photograph of the staff at Giles County Hospital. Dr. D. M. Spotwood, one of only two Black physicians in Giles County, is seated on the far right. A decorated Christmas tree is behind the group.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Physicians; Health care personnel; Group portraits
